<eesti>Riiklike peretoetuste seadus </eesti>
<inglise>State Family Benefits Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 14. novembril 2001. a </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 14 November 2001 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2001, 95, 587), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2001, 95, 587), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. jaanuaril 2002. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 January 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse eesm&auml;rk ja reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose and scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklike peretoetuste seaduse eesm&auml;rk on tagada lastega peredele laste hooldamise, kasvatamise ja &otilde;ppimisega seotud kulutuste osaline h&uuml;vitamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The purpose of the State Family Benefits Act is to ensure for families with children the partial reimbursement of expenses relating to the care, raising and education of children. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab riiklike peretoetuste (edaspidi peretoetused) liigid, ulatuse, saamise tingimused ja korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act provides the classification and extent of state family benefits (hereinafter family benefits), and the conditions and procedure for the grant thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidemenetluse s&auml;testab haldusmenetluse seadus (RT I 2001, 58, 354), kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>Challenge procedure is provided for in the Administrative Procedure Act (RT I 2001, 58, 354), unless otherwise provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui Eesti Vabariigi s&otilde;lmitud v&auml;lisleping sisaldab peretoetuste saamise tingimuste ja korra ning vaidemenetluse kohta k&auml;esolevast seadusest erinevaid s&auml;tteid, kohaldatakse v&auml;lislepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an international agreement entered into by the Republic of Estonia includes provisions concerning the conditions and procedure for the grant of family benefits and the challenge procedure which are different from this Act, the international agreement applies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetustele &otilde;igust omavad isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Persons with right to receive family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetusi m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja makstakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Family benefits are granted and paid, under the conditions provided for in this Act, to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Eesti alalisele elanikule; </eesti>
<inglise>1) permanent residents of Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Eestis elavale v&auml;lismaalasele, kellel on t&auml;htajaline elamisluba v&otilde;i kes viibib Eestis v&auml;lismaalaste seaduse (RT I 1993, 44, 637; 1999, 50, 548; 54, 582; 71, 686; 88, 808; 101, 900; 2000, 25, 148; 33, 197; 40, 254; 2001, 16, 68; RT III 2001, 7, 75; RT I 2001, 58, 352) &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 1 (1) s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) aliens residing in Estonia who have temporary residence permits or who stay in Estonia on the basis provided for in subsection 9 (1 (1)) of the Aliens Act (RT I 1993, 44, 637; 1999, 50, 548; 54, 582; 71, 686; 88, 808; 101, 900; 2000, 25, 148; 33, 197; 40, 254; 2001, 16, 68; RT III 2001, 7, 75; RT I 2001, 58, 352). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Peretoetustele on &otilde;igus Eestis elavatel perekonnaliikmetel ja v&auml;lismaal &otilde;ppimise t&otilde;ttu perest eemalviibivatel lastel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Family members residing in Estonia and children who do not live in the family due to studying abroad have the right to receive family benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Peretoetusi ei maksta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud perekonnaliikme kohta, kes saab m&otilde;ne teise riigi vastavat toetust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Family benefits shall not be paid for family members specified in subsection (2) of this section if they receive the corresponding benefits of another state. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igakuiselt makstavad peretoetused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Monthly family benefits are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lapsetoetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) child allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lapsehooldustasu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) child care allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) single parent's child allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ajateenija lapse toetus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) conscript's child allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>5) eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetus. </eesti>
<inglise>5) foster care allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;hekordselt makstavad peretoetused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Single family benefits are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&uuml;nnitoetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) childbirth allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lapsendamistoetus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) adoption allowance; </inglise>
<eesti>3) elluastumistoetus. </eesti>
<inglise>3) start in independent life allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kord kvartalis makstav peretoetus on nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets is a family benefit which is paid once per quarter. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kord aastas makstav peretoetus on koolitoetus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) School allowance is a family benefit which is paid once a year. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui isikul on &otilde;igus saada mitut liiki peretoetusi, m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja makstakse neid toetusi samaaegselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a person has the right to receive several classes of family benefits, the benefits shall be granted and paid at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste finantseerimine, lapsetoetuse ja lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of family benefits, child allowance rate and child care allowance rate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetusi finantseeritakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Family benefits are financed from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Peretoetuste, v&auml;lja arvatud lapsehooldustasu arvutamise aluseks on lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;r, mis kehtestatakse igaks eelarveaastaks riigieelarvega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The basis for calculation of family benefits, except the child care allowance, shall be the child allowance rate established by the state budget for each budgetary year. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsetoetuse uus m&auml;&auml;r ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem kehtivast m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>A new child allowance rate shall not be less than the rate in force. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lapsehooldustasu arvutamise aluseks on lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;r, mis kehtestatakse igaks eelarveaastaks riigieelarvega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The basis for calculation of child care allowances shall be the child care allowance rate established by the state budget for each budgetary year. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehooldustasu uus m&auml;&auml;r ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem kehtivast m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>A new child care allowance rate shall not be less than the rate in force. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Igakuiselt makstavad peretoetused </eesti>
<inglise>Monthly Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsetoetus </eesti>
<inglise>Child allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapsetoetusele on &otilde;igus igal lapsel s&uuml;ndimisest kuni 16-aastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Every child has the right to receive child allowance from the birth until he or she attains 16 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lapsel, kes &otilde;pib p&auml;evases &otilde;ppevormis v&otilde;i meditsiinilistel n&auml;idustustel muus &otilde;ppevormis p&otilde;hikoolis v&otilde;i g&uuml;mnaasiumis v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikooli baasil kutse&otilde;ppeasutuses, on &otilde;igus lapsetoetusele kuni 19-aastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A child who is enrolled in a basic school, upper secondary school or vocational school which operates on the basis of basic education, in daytime study or, for medical reasons, in another form of study has the right to receive child allowance until he or she attains 19 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>19-aastaseks saamisel makstakse toetust jooksva &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>When the child attains 19 years of age, the allowance shall be paid until the end of the school year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lapsetoetust makstakse pere esimese lapse kohta &uuml;hekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras, teise ja iga j&auml;rgneva lapse kohta kahekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Child allowance shall be paid to a first child at the child allowance rate and to a second and each subsequent child at twice the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehooldustasu </eesti>
<inglise>Child care allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapsehooldustasule on &otilde;igus &uuml;hel vanematest, kes: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) One of the parents has the right to receive child care allowance: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kasvatab &uuml;hte v&otilde;i enamat kuni kolmeaastast last - pooles lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ras iga kuni kolmeaastase lapse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at one-half of the child care allowance rate for each child of up to 3 years of age if the parent raises one or more children of up to 3 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kasvatab lisaks &uuml;hele v&otilde;i enamale kuni kolmeaastasele lapsele ka kolme kuni kaheksa-aastaseid lapsi - &uuml;hes neljandikus lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ras iga kolme kuni kaheksa-aastase lapse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) at one-quarter of the child care allowance rate for each child between 3 and 8 years of age if the parent raises also children between 3 and 8 years of age in addition to one or more children of up to 3 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kasvatab kolme- ja enamalapselises perekonnas kolme v&otilde;i enamat lapsetoetust saavat v&auml;hemalt kolmeaastast last - &uuml;hes neljandikus lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ras iga kolme kuni kaheksa-aastase lapse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>3) at one-quarter of the child care allowance rate for each child between 3 and 8 years of age if the parent raises three or more children who are at least 3 years of age and who receive child allowance in a family with three or more children. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 2 ja 3 alusel &uuml;heaegselt sama lapse kohta toetust ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An allowance shall not be paid for the same child pursuant to both clauses (1) 2) and 3) of this section at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud laps l&auml;heb esimesse klassi ja saab jooksval &otilde;ppeaastal kaheksa-aastaseks, makstakse selle lapse kohta lapsehooldustasu &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a child specified in clauses (1) 2) or 3) of this section starts year one at school and attains 8 years of age during the given school year, child care allowance for the child shall be paid until the end of the school year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui &uuml;ks vanematest on lapsehoolduspuhkusel, on &otilde;igus lapsehooldustasule sellel vanemal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If one of the parents is on parental leave, that parent has the right to receive child care allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui lapsehoolduspuhkust kasutab vanema asemel m&otilde;ni teine isik, on tal &otilde;igus lapsehooldustasule pooles lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ras iga hooldatava lapse kohta, kuid kokku mitte rohkem kui poolteisekordses lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If a person other than a parent uses parental leave, that person has the right to receive child care allowance at one-half of the child care allowance rate for each child in his or her care, but not more than one and one-half times the child care allowance rate in total. </inglise>
<eesti>Vanemale sama lapse kohta selle aja eest lapsehooldustasu ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>For such period, child care allowance shall not be paid to the parent for the same child. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Lapse eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud kirjalik perekonnas hooldamise leping (edaspidi hooldaja), on &otilde;igus lapsehooldustasule k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A guardian or caregiver of a child with respect to whom a written foster care contract has been entered into (hereinafter caregiver) has the right to receive child care allowance under the conditions provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetus </eesti>
<inglise>Single parent's child allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetusele on &otilde;igus lapsel, kelle s&uuml;nniaktis puudub kanne isa kohta v&otilde;i see on tehtud ema &uuml;tluse alusel v&otilde;i kelle vanem on seadusega kehtestatud korras tunnistatud tagaotsitavaks ja kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A child in whose birth registration no entry has been made concerning the father or an entry has been made on the basis of a statement by the mother or whose parent has been declared to be a fugitive pursuant to the procedure established by law and who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act has the right to receive a single parent's child allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetust makstakse kahekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Single parent's child allowance shall be paid at twice the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajateenija lapse toetus </eesti>
<inglise>Conscript's child allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ajateenija lapse toetusele on &otilde;igus Eesti kaitsej&otilde;ududes ajateenistuses oleva isiku lapsel, kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A child of a conscript in the service of the Defence Forces who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act has the right to receive conscript's child allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ajateenija lapse toetust makstakse viiekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Conscript's child allowance shall be paid at five times the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetus </eesti>
<inglise>Foster care allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetusele on &otilde;igus vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsel, kelle &uuml;le on seatud eestkoste v&otilde;i kelle suhtes on s&otilde;lmitud kirjalik perekonnas hooldamise leping ja kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Foster care allowance shall be paid for a child who is deprived of parental care, if guardianship has been established for him or her or a foster care contract has been entered into with respect to him or her, and who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestkoste v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamise l&otilde;ppemisel seoses lapse 18-aastaseks saamisega makstakse toetust selle jooksva &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;puni, mil laps saab 19-aastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon termination of guardianship or foster care when a child attains 18 years of age, payment of an allowance shall continue until the end of the school year when the child attains 19 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetust makstakse kuuekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Foster care allowance shall be paid at six times the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hekordselt makstavad peretoetused </eesti>
<inglise>Single Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;nnitoetus </eesti>
<inglise>Childbirth allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;nnitoetusele on &otilde;igus &uuml;hel vanematest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) One of the parents has the right to receive childbirth allowance: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esimese lapse s&uuml;nni korral - kahek&uuml;mne viie kordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at twenty-five times the child allowance rate, for a first child; </inglise>
<eesti>2) iga j&auml;rgmise lapse s&uuml;nni korral - kahek&uuml;mnekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>2) at twenty times the child allowance rate, for each subsequent child. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mitmikute s&uuml;nni korral makstakse s&uuml;nnitoetust iga lapse kohta kahek&uuml;mne viie kordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a multiple birth, childbirth allowance shall be paid at twenty-five times the child allowance rate for each child. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;nnitoetust ei maksta, kui laps s&uuml;ndis surnult. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Childbirth allowance shall not be paid if the child is stillborn. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&uuml;nnitoetusele on &otilde;igus lapsendajal, eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal, kui varem ei ole sama lapse kohta s&uuml;nnitoetust makstud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An adoptive parent, guardian or caregiver has the right to receive childbirth allowance, if childbirth allowance has not been paid for the same child earlier. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsendamistoetus </eesti>
<inglise>Adoption allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapsendamistoetusele on &otilde;igus Eestis alaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;htajalise elamisloaga elaval lapsendajal, kellest lapsendatav laps ei p&otilde;lvne ja kes ei ole selle lapse v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanem, kui varem ei ole sellele perele sama lapse kohta s&uuml;nnitoetust makstud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An adoptive parent residing in Estonia permanently or on the basis of a temporary residence permit from who an adopted child does not descend and who is not a step-parent of the child has the right to receive adoption allowance, if childbirth allowance has not been paid to the family for the same child earlier. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lapsendamistoetust makstakse kahek&uuml;mnekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Adoption allowance shall be paid at twenty times the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Elluastumistoetus </eesti>
<inglise>Start in independent life allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elluastumistoetusele on &otilde;igus lapsena hoolekandeasutuses v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste koolis kasvanud vanemliku hoolitsuseta isikul, kui ta asub uude elukohta iseseisvalt elama. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person without parental care who has been raised in a social welfare institution or a school for children with special needs has the right to receive a start in independent life allowance if he or she begins to live independently in a new residence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elluastumistoetust makstakse neljak&uuml;mnekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Start in independent life allowance shall be paid at forty times the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on elanud hoolekandeasutuses v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste koolis alla kolme aasta, v&auml;hendatakse elluastumistoetust iga v&auml;hem oldud kuu eest 2,5 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person specified in subsection (1) of this section has resided in a social welfare institution or a school for children with special needs for less than three years, the start in independent life allowance shall be reduced by 2.5 per cent for each month less than three years. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Muud peretoetused </eesti>
<inglise>Other Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetus </eesti>
<inglise>Allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetust on &otilde;igus saada &uuml;hel vanematest, kes kasvatab nelja v&otilde;i enamat lapsetoetust saavat last v&otilde;i lapsetoetust saavaid kolmikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) One of the parents raising four or more children who receive child allowance, or one of the parents raising triplets who receive child allowance has the right to receive an allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Nelja- ja enamalapselisele perele makstakse toetust &uuml;hekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras iga lapse kohta, kes jooksva kalendriaasta antud kvartalis vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An allowance shall be paid at the child allowance rate to a family with four or more children for each child who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act within the given quarter of the calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kolmikuid kasvatavale perele makstakse toetust neljakordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras, kui iga laps jooksva kalendriaasta antud kvartalis vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An allowance shall be paid at four times the child allowance rate to a family raising triplets if each of their children meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act within the given quarter of the calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 alusel &uuml;heaegselt toetust ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An allowance shall not be paid pursuant to both subsections (2) and (3) of this section at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lapse eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal on &otilde;igus nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetusele k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A guardian or caregiver of a child has the right to receive an allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets under the conditions provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitoetus </eesti>
<inglise>School allowance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolitoetust on &otilde;igus saada &otilde;ppeaasta alustamiseks lapsel, kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A child who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act has the right to receive school allowance for the commencement of the school year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitoetust makstakse kolmekordses lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) School allowance shall be paid at three times the child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste taotleja </eesti>
<inglise>Applicant for family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetusi taotleb lapse ema, isa, eestkostja, hooldaja v&otilde;i: </eesti>
<inglise>The mother, father, guardian or caregiver of a child or one of the following persons may apply for family benefits: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vanema asemel lapsehoolduspuhkust kasutav isik; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person, other than a parent, who uses parental leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) last kasvatav v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanem v&otilde;i kasuvanem valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse korralduse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a step-parent or foster parent raising the child, on the basis of an order by a rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hoolekandeasutusest &otilde;ppimise t&otilde;ttu eemalviibiv v&auml;hemalt 15-aastane vanemliku hoolitsuseta laps; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a child without parental care who is at least 15 years of age and does not stay in a social welfare institution due to studying; </inglise>
<eesti>4) hoolekandeasutusest v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste koolist uude elukohta iseseisvalt elama asunud vanemliku hoolitsuseta olnud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a person without parental care who has been raised in a social welfare institution or a school for children with special needs and who begins to live independently in a new residence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste taotlemiseks vajalikud dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents necessary for application for family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetuste taotlemiseks esitatakse j&auml;rgmised p&otilde;hidokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following basic documents shall be submitted for application for family benefits: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikut t&otilde;endavate dokumentide seaduse (RT I 1999, 25, 365; 2000, 25, 148; 26, 150; 40, 254; 86, 550; 2001, 16, 68; 31, 173; 56, 338) &sect; 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud dokument; Eestis elav v&auml;lismaalane peab esitama dokumendi, milles on m&auml;rge alalise v&otilde;i kehtiva t&auml;htajalise elamisloa kohta, v&otilde;i selle puudumise korral p&auml;deva asutuse kirjaliku t&otilde;endi tema seadusliku viibimise kohta Eesti Vabariigis; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a document provided for in subsection 2 (2) of the Identity Documents Act (RT I 1999, 25, 365; 2000, 25, 148; 26, 150; 40, 254; 86, 550; 2001, 16, 68; 31, 173; 56, 338); an alien residing in Estonia shall submit a document which contains a notation concerning a permanent or valid temporary residence permit or, in the absence thereof, a written certificate of a competent agency concerning his or her legal stay in the Republic of Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lapse s&uuml;nnitunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the birth certificate of the child; </inglise>
<eesti>4) 16-aastase v&otilde;i vanema &otilde;pilase &otilde;pilaspilet v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatis. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the student card or a statement from the educational institution in the case of a student not less than 16 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Peretoetuste taotlemise avalduse vormi ja vajalike lisadokumentide loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the format of applications for family benefits and the list of necessary additional documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vajaduse korral on pensioniametil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda peretoetuste taotlejalt t&auml;iendavaid dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If necessary, the Pension Board has the right to require additional documents from applicants for family benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Peretoetuste taotlemiseks esitatakse originaaldokumendid v&otilde;i notariaalselt kinnitatud &auml;rakirjad v&otilde;i v&auml;ljav&otilde;tted. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Original documents or notarially certified copies or extracts shall be submitted upon application for family benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioniamet kinnitab originaaldokumendi koopia, mis j&auml;etakse pensioniametisse. </eesti>
<inglise>The Pension Board shall certify the copies of original documents to be kept by the Pension Board. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;ik originaaldokumendid tagastatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>All original documents shall be returned. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetuste taotlemiseks esitab peretoetuste taotleja (edaspidi taotleja) taotluse oma elukohaj&auml;rgsele pensioniametile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to apply for family benefits, an applicant for family benefits (hereinafter applicant) shall submit an application to the local pension office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotleja elukohaks on rahvastikuregistrisse kantud elukoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The residence which is entered in the population register is deemed to be the residence of the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui taotlejal ei ole registrij&auml;rgset elukohta, m&auml;&auml;ratleb taotleja oma elukoha ise. </eesti>
<inglise>If the residence of an applicant is not entered in the register, the applicant shall determine his or her residence himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 punktis 3 nimetatud isik esitab taotluse &otilde;ppeasutuse asukohaj&auml;rgsele pensioniametile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person specified in clause 15 3) of this Act shall submit an application to the pension office of the location of the educational institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Toetuste taotlemise p&auml;evaks loetakse taotluse vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The date on which an application is received is deemed to be the date of application for benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui taotlus on saadetud posti teel, loetakse toetuste taotlemise p&auml;evaks taotluse l&auml;htekoha postitempli kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>If the application is sent by post, the date on the date stamp of the place from which the application is sent is deemed to be the date of application for benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of applications </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensioniamet vaatab peretoetuste taotlemiseks esitatud dokumendid l&auml;bi esimesel v&otilde;imalusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Pension Board shall review the documents submitted for application for family benefits at the earliest opportunity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui taotlusele ei ole lisatud k&otilde;iki vajalikke dokumente v&otilde;i esitatud dokumentides on puudusi, m&auml;&auml;rab pensioniamet taotlejale esimesel v&otilde;imalusel t&auml;htaja puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If not all the necessary documents have been appended to an application or the submitted documents contain deficiencies, the Pension Board shall, at the first opportunity, designate a term to the applicant for elimination of the deficiencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui taotleja k&otilde;rvaldab puudused pensioniameti m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks, loetakse toetuste taotlemise p&auml;evaks taotluse vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;ev v&otilde;i taotluse l&auml;htekoha postitempli kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an applicant eliminates deficiencies within the term designated by the Pension Board, the date on which the application is received or the date on the date stamp of the place from which the application is sent is deemed to be the date of application for benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui taotleja ei k&otilde;rvalda puudusi m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul, teeb pensioniamet otsuse olemasolevate dokumentide alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>If the applicant fails to eliminate deficiencies within the designated term, the Pension Board shall make a decision on the basis of the existing documents. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste suuruse kindlakstegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Determination of amount of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetuste suuruse kindlakstegemisel v&otilde;etakse arvesse k&otilde;ik peres kasvavad lapsetoetusele &otilde;igust omavad lapsed, neist vanimat loetakse esimeseks lapseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to determine the amount of family benefits, all children raised in a family who have the right to receive child allowance shall be taken into account and the eldest is deemed to be the first child. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puudest tingitud erivajaduse v&otilde;i &otilde;ppimise t&otilde;ttu ajutiselt perest eemalviibiv laps loetakse peretoetuste suuruse kindlakstegemisel pere koosseisu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon determination of the amount of family benefits, a child who temporarily does not live in the family due to special needs caused by the disability or due to studying is deemed to be a member of the family. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Peretoetuste suuruse kindlakstegemisel ei arvata peretoetusi taotleva vanema pere koosseisu last: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon determination of the amount of family benefits, the following children are not deemed to be members of the family of a parent applying for family benefits: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kes elab lahus elava vanema, v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanema v&otilde;i kasuvanema juures; </eesti>
<inglise>1) children who are residing with a parent, step-parent or foster parent living apart; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kes on teises perekonnas eestkostel v&otilde;i hooldamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) children who are under guardianship or foster care in another family; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kes on lapsendatud teise peresse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) children who are adopted by another family; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kes elab pidevalt hoolekandeasutuses. </eesti>
<inglise>4) children who permanently reside in a social welfare institution. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Hoolekandeasutusest &otilde;ppimise t&otilde;ttu eemalviibiv vanemliku hoolitsuseta laps loetakse lapsetoetuse suuruse kindlakstegemisel esimeseks lapseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon determination of the amount of child allowance, a child without parental care who does not stay in a social welfare institution due to studying is deemed to be the first child. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste arvutamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for calculation of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapsetoetuse, &uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetuse, ajateenija lapse toetuse ja eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetuse suurus arvutatakse toetuse m&auml;&auml;ramise algt&auml;htajal kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The amount of child allowance, single parent's child allowance, conscript's child allowance and foster care allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force on the date of grant of the allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra muutmise korral arvutatakse toetus &uuml;mber uue lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra kehtestamise kuup&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon amendment of the child allowance rate, the allowance shall be recalculated as of the date of establishment of a new child allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lapsehooldustasu suurus arvutatakse toetuse m&auml;&auml;ramise algt&auml;htajal kehtinud lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The amount of child care allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force on the date of grant of the allowance. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ra muutmise korral arvutatakse toetus &uuml;mber uue lapsehooldustasu m&auml;&auml;ra kehtestamise kuup&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon amendment of the child care allowance rate, the allowance shall be recalculated as of the date of establishment of a new child care allowance rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;nnitoetuse suurus arvutatakse lapse s&uuml;nnikuup&auml;eval kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount of childbirth allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force on the date of birth of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lapsendamistoetuse suurus arvutatakse lapsendamise kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;eval kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The amount of adoption allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force on the date of entry into force of the court judgment on adoption. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Elluastumistoetuse suurus arvutatakse uude elukohta elama asumise kuup&auml;eval kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The amount of start in independent life allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force on the date of moving to a new residence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetuse suurus arvutatakse toetuse m&auml;&auml;ramise kvartali viimasel kuul kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The amount of allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force in the last month of the quarter when the allowance is granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Koolitoetuse suurus arvutatakse &otilde;ppeaasta alguskuule eelneval kuul kehtinud lapsetoetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The amount of school allowance shall be calculated on the basis of the child allowance rate in force within the month preceding the month when the school year begins. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term for grant of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igakuiselt makstav peretoetus m&auml;&auml;ratakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud toetusele &otilde;iguse tekkimise p&auml;evast, kui toetuse taotlemiseks vajalikud dokumendid on esitatud kuue kuu jooksul, arvates toetusele &otilde;iguse tekkimise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A monthly family benefit shall be granted from the date on which the right to the benefit provided for in this Act arises if the documents necessary for application for the benefit are submitted within six months from the date on which the right to the benefit arises. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igakuiselt makstava peretoetuse hilisemal taotlemisel m&auml;&auml;ratakse toetus tagantj&auml;rele, kuid mitte rohkem kui taotluse esitamise kuule eelnenud kuue kalendrikuu eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon a later application for a monthly family benefit, the benefit shall be granted retroactively, but for not more than the six calendar months preceding the month of submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;nnitoetus m&auml;&auml;ratakse, kui toetust on taotletud kuue kuu jooksul, alates lapse s&uuml;nnist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Childbirth allowance shall be granted if the allowance has been applied for within six months as of the birth of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lapsendamistoetus m&auml;&auml;ratakse, kui toetust on taotletud kuue kuu jooksul, alates lapsendamise kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Adoption allowance shall be granted if the allowance has been applied for within six months as of entry into force of the court judgment on adoption. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Elluastumistoetus m&auml;&auml;ratakse, kui toetust on taotletud hiljemalt kahe aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel vanemliku hoolitsuseta olnud lapse hoolekandeasutuse v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste kooli kasvandike nimekirjast kustutamisest ja uude elukohta elama asumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Start in independent life allowance shall be granted if the allowance has been applied for not later than within two years after a child who has been deprived of parental care is deleted from the list of children raised in a social welfare institution or school for children with special needs and after the child moves to a new residence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Koolitoetus m&auml;&auml;ratakse 16-aastasele ja vanemale lapsele, kui toetust on taotletud kuue kuu jooksul, arvates &otilde;ppeaasta algusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) School allowance shall be granted to children not less than 16 years of age if the allowance has been applied for within six months after the beginning of the school year. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Peretoetused m&auml;&auml;ratakse taotlejale ajaks, mil isik vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Family benefits shall be granted for the period during which a person fulfils the conditions provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramise otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Decision to grant family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise otsustab pensioniamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Pension Board shall decide on the grant of family benefits or refusal to grant family benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetused m&auml;&auml;ratakse toetuste taotlejale, kes vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>Family benefits shall be granted to an applicant who fulfils the conditions provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Toetuse taotleja n&otilde;udmisel v&otilde;i kollegiaalset lahendust n&otilde;udva taotluse puhul otsustab toetuse m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise pensioniametis riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse alusel moodustatud pensionikomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the request of an applicant, or in the case of an application which requires a collegial decision, the grant of the benefit or refusal to grant the benefit shall be decided by a pension committee formed in the Pension Board pursuant to the State Pension Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i mittem&auml;&auml;ramise otsus vormistatakse kirjalikult kahes eksemplaris, mis koosneb: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision to grant or to refuse to grant family benefits shall be prepared in writing in two original copies and shall consist of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sissejuhatusest, milles m&auml;rgitakse otsuse teinud pensioniameti direktori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i pensioniameti direktori volitatud struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juhi nimi v&otilde;i pensionikomisjoni nimi, koosseis ja otsuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an introduction which sets out the name of the director or deputy director of the Pension Board, or the head of a structural unit authorised by the director of the Pension Board, who makes the decision, or the name and membership of the pension committee which makes the decision and the date on which the decision is made; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kirjeldavast osast, mis sisaldab kokkuv&otilde;tet toetuse taotleja taotlusest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a descriptive part which contains a summary of the application of the applicant for benefits; </inglise>
<eesti>3) otsuse p&otilde;hjendusest, milles m&auml;rgitakse dokumendid ja t&otilde;endid, samuti asjaolud, millele otsus on rajatud ning viited otsuse aluseks olevate &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the reasons of the decision which indicate the documents and evidence, and circumstances and reference to the provisions of legislation on which the decision is based; </inglise>
<eesti>4) otsuse resolutsioonist, mis sisaldab seisukohta toetuse taotluse rahuldamise v&otilde;i rahuldamata j&auml;tmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the conclusion of the decision which includes an opinion on the satisfaction of or refusal to satisfy the application; </inglise>
<eesti>5) selgitusest otsuse vaidlustamise korra ja t&auml;htaja kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) information on the procedure and term for contestation against the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>6) m&auml;rkest otsuse k&auml;ttetoimetamise viisi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a notation concerning the manner of delivery of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>7) otsuse teinud ametniku v&otilde;i ametnike allkirjadest. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the signature of the official or officials who made the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramisest keeldumisest teatatakse taotlejale kirjalikult viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant shall be notified of refusal to grant family benefits in writing within five working days as of the date on which the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramata j&auml;tmise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Grounds for refusal to grant family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetusi ei m&auml;&auml;rata, kui peretoetuste saamiseks kehtestatud tingimused ei ole t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise>Family benefits shall not be granted if the conditions established for the grant of family benefits are not fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of Family Benefits </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peretoetusi makstakse elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti kaudu igakuiselt jooksva kuu eest vastavalt toetuste saaja soovile panka tema arvele v&otilde;i posti teel maksja kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Family benefits shall be paid monthly for the current month through a local pension office either to the bank account of the recipient of the benefits or by post at the expense of the payer of the benefits as requested by the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Peretoetuste maksmist j&auml;tkatakse lapse 16-aastaseks saamisel p&auml;rast &otilde;pilaspileti v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise esitamist kuni uue &otilde;ppeaasta algusele eelneva p&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Payment of family benefits shall continue when a child attains 16 years of age after submission of a student card or a statement from an educational institution until the day which precedes the beginning of a school year. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast nimetatud t&auml;htaega esitatakse peretoetuste saamiseks pikendatud kehtivusajaga &otilde;pilaspilet v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatis uue &otilde;ppeaasta esimese kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>After the specified term, an extended student card or a statement from an educational institution shall be submitted within the first month of the school year in order to receive the family benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Hilisemal &otilde;pilaspileti v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise esitamisel makstakse toetusi tagasiulatuvalt, kuid mitte rohkem kui dokumendi esitamisele eelnenud kuue kuu eest. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon later submission of a student card or a statement from an educational institution, benefits shall be paid retroactively, but for not more than the six months preceding the submission of the document. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui 16-aastane v&otilde;i vanem laps l&otilde;petab p&otilde;hikooli, g&uuml;mnaasiumi v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikooli baasil kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse, l&otilde;petatakse peretoetuste maksmine kooli l&otilde;petamisele j&auml;rgnevast kuust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a child who is not less than 16 years of age graduates from a basic school, upper secondary school or vocational school which operates on the basis of basic education, payment of family benefits shall be terminated as of the month following the graduation. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pingute j&auml;tkamisel samal kalendriaastal &otilde;ppeasutuses, kus &otilde;ppimine annab &otilde;iguse peretoetustele, makstakse p&auml;rast &otilde;pilaspileti v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise esitamist toetusi tagasiulatuvalt toetuste maksmise l&otilde;petamisest kuni uuesti &otilde;ppima asumiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon continuation of studies in an educational institution during the same calendar year, if studying in the educational institution grants the right to receive family benefits, benefits shall be paid retroactively after submission of a student card or a statement from the educational institution for the period from termination of payment of benefits until re-commencement of studies. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Koolitoetust makstakse jooksva aasta 1. oktoobriks seitsmeaastaseks saanud lapsele &otilde;ppeasutuse teatist v&otilde;i &otilde;pilaspiletit esitamata kuni lapse 16-aastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) School allowance shall be paid to a child who attains 7 years of age by 1 October of the current year until the child attains 16 years of age without submission of a statement from an educational institution or a student card. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapse varasema koolimineku korral makstakse koolitoetust &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise v&otilde;i &otilde;pilaspileti esitamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon earlier school entry, school allowance shall be paid upon submission of a statement from an educational institution or a student card. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapse hilisema koolimineku korral on toetust saanud isik kohustatud sellest pensioniametile kirjalikult teatama. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon later school entry, the recipient of the allowance is required to inform the Pension Board thereof in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) 16-aastasele ja vanemale lapsele makstakse koolitoetust p&auml;rast &otilde;pilaspileti v&otilde;i &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise esitamist uue &otilde;ppeaasta esimese kuu jooksul, kuid mitte hiljem kui kuue kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel &otilde;ppeaasta algusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) School allowance shall be paid to a child who is not less than 16 years of age after submission of a student card or a statement from an educational institution within the first month of the school year, but not later than six months after the beginning of the school year. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Nelja- ja enamalapselise pere ning kolmikuid kasvatava pere toetust makstakse, s&otilde;ltumata neljale ja enamale lapsele v&otilde;i kolmikutele lapsetoetuse maksmise aja kestusest selles kvartalis. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An allowance for families with four or more children and families raising triplets shall be paid regardless of the duration of payment of the child allowance to four or more children or triplets within that quarter. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetus makstakse v&auml;lja jooksva kalendriaasta iga kvartali viimases kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>An allowance shall be paid out within the last month of each quarter of the given calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Toetusesaaja surma p&auml;evaks saamata j&auml;&auml;nud peretoetus makstakse teisele isikule tema taotluse alusel, kui ta vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustele, kuid mitte rohkem kui taotluse esitamisele eelnenud kuue kuu eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Family benefits not received by the date of death of a recipient of benefits shall be paid to another person on the basis of his or her application if he or she fulfils the conditions provided for in this Act, but for not more than the six months preceding the submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Toetuste maksmisel &uuml;mardatakse 50 ja rohkem senti kroonini, alla 50-sendist summat ei arvestata. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Upon payment of benefits, amounts of 50 sents and more shall be rounded to one kroon, and amounts of less than 50 sents shall not be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste maksmise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of payment of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsele, kes elab pidevalt hoolekandeasutuses v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste koolis, peretoetusi ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Family benefits shall not be paid to a child without parental care who permanently resides in a social welfare institution or a school for children with special needs. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoolekandeasutusest &otilde;ppimise t&otilde;ttu eemalviibivale vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsele makstakse lapsetoetust, &uuml;ksikvanema lapse toetust ja koolitoetust, kui ta vastab nimetatud toetuste saamiseks k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>Child allowance, single parent's child allowance and school allowance shall be paid to a child without parental care who does not stay in a social welfare institution due to studying if he or she fulfils the conditions for receiving the specified allowances provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puudest tingitud erivajaduse t&otilde;ttu ajutiselt hoolekandeasutuses v&otilde;i erivajadustega laste koolis viibiva lapse kohta makstakse peretoetusi, v&auml;lja arvatud lapsehooldustasu ja eestkostel v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamisel oleva lapse toetust, kui laps vastab toetuste saamiseks k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Family benefits, except child care allowance and foster care allowance, shall be paid for a child who temporarily stays in a social welfare institution or a school for children with special needs due to special needs caused by a disability, if the child fulfils the conditions for receiving the specified benefits provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lja v&otilde;tmata peretoetuste maksmise peatamine ja j&auml;tkamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension and continuation of payment of family benefits which are not collected </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioniamet peatab toetuste maksmise, kui posti teel makstavad toetused on v&auml;lja v&otilde;tmata v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>The Pension Board shall suspend payment of benefits if the benefits paid by post are not collected for at least six months. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast vastava taotluse ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 s&auml;testatud dokumendi esitamist makstakse toetus taotlejale v&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise>After submission of a corresponding application and a document provided for in clause 16 (1) 2) of this Act, the benefits shall be paid to the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Elukohta vahetanud toetusesaajale peretoetuste maksmise j&auml;tkamine </eesti>
<inglise>Continuation of payment of family benefits to recipient of benefits who has changed residence </inglise>
<eesti>Elukohta vahetanud toetusesaajale j&auml;tkatakse peretoetuste maksmist p&auml;rast vastava taotluse ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 s&auml;testatud dokumendi esitamist uue elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti kaudu ajast, mil maksmine endises kohas l&otilde;petati. </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of family benefits to a recipient of benefits who has changed his or her residence shall continue after submission of a corresponding application and a document provided for in clause 16 (1) 2) of this Act through a new local pension office as of the time when payment in the former place is terminated. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsele etten&auml;htud peretoetuste maksmise peatamine ja j&auml;tkamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension and continuation of payment of family benefits prescribed for children without parental care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensioniamet peatab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse korraldusel ajutiselt peretoetuste maksmise, kui lapsevanem ei t&auml;ida perekonnaseadusest (RT I 1994, 75, 1326; 1996, 40, 773; 49, 953; 1997, 28, 422; 35, 538; 2000, 50, 317; 2001, 16, 69; RT III 2001, 15, 154; RT I 2001, 53, 307) tulenevat kohustust last kasvatada ja tema eest hoolitseda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Pension Board shall temporarily suspend payment of family benefits on the basis of an order by a rural municipality or city government if a parent does not fulfil the duty arising from the Family Law Act (RT I 1994, 75, 1326; 1996, 40, 773; 49, 953; 1997, 28, 422; 35, 538; 2000, 50, 317; 2001, 16, 69; RT III 2001, 15, 154; RT I 2001, 53, 307) to raise a child and to care for him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pensioniamet j&auml;tkab peretoetuste maksmist lapse vanemale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjuste &auml;ralangemisel valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse korralduse v&otilde;i kohtuotsuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the reasons specified in subsection (1) of this section cease to exist, the Pension Board shall continue to pay family benefits to the parent on the basis of an order by a rural municipality or city government or on the basis of a court judgment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pensioniamet j&auml;tkab vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsele etten&auml;htud peretoetuste maksmist v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemale v&otilde;i kasuvanemale v&otilde;i eestkostjale v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldajale valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse korralduse v&otilde;i kohtuotsuse v&otilde;i perekonnas hooldamise lepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Pension Board shall continue payment of family benefits prescribed for a child without parental care to a step-parent, foster parent, guardian or foster family on the basis of an order by a rural municipality or city government, a court judgment or a foster care contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pensioniamet j&auml;tkab peretoetuste maksmist iseseisvalt elama asunud vanemliku hoolitsuseta lapsele, kes vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustele, valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse korralduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Pension Board shall continue payment of family benefits to a child without parental care who begins to live independently and who meets the requirements provided for in subsection 5 (1) or (2) of this Act on the basis of an order by a rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Peretoetuste maksmise j&auml;tkamisel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 s&auml;testatud juhtudel makstakse peretoetusi tagantj&auml;rele mitte rohkem kui vastava taotluse esitamise kuule eelnenud kuue kalendrikuu eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon continuation of payment of family benefits in the cases provided for in subsections (3) and (4) of this section, the benefits shall be paid retroactively for not more than the six calendar months preceding the submission of the corresponding application. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui laps viibis peretoetuste maksmise peatamise ajal hoolekandeasutuses, siis hoolekandeasutuses viibimise aja eest toetust tagantj&auml;rele ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If, during suspension of payment of family benefits, a child stays in a social welfare institution, the benefits shall not be paid retroactively for the period the child stayed in the social welfare institution. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste maksmise muutmine ja l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Change in and termination of payment of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Asjaoludest, mis m&otilde;jutavad peretoetuste saamist v&otilde;i toetuste suurust, on toetuste saaja kohustatud elukohaj&auml;rgsele pensioniametile kirjalikult teatama k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates nende asjaolude tekkimise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The recipient of benefits is required to notify the local pension office of circumstances which affect the grant of family benefits or the amount of benefits in writing within ten days after the circumstances arise. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui lapse vanem on seadusega kehtestatud korras tunnistatud tagaotsitavaks ning tagaotsimine l&otilde;petatakse, on tagaotsimisega tegelev asutus kohustatud saatma pensioniametile teate tagaotsimise l&otilde;petamise kohta viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates tagaotsimise l&otilde;petamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a parent is declared to be a fugitive pursuant to the procedure established by law and the search is terminated, an agency engaged in searching is required to send a notice on termination of the search to the Pension Board within five working days as of termination of the search. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud asjaolude ilmnemisel &uuml;hekordselt makstavat peretoetust, kord kvartalis v&otilde;i kord aastas makstavat peretoetust ei maksta; igakuiselt makstava toetuse maksmine l&otilde;petatakse asjaolude tekkimise kuule j&auml;rgnevast kuust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If circumstances provided for in subsection (1) of this section become evident, a single family benefit or a family benefit paid once per quarter or once a year shall not be paid; payment of a monthly benefit shall be terminated as of the month following the month in which such circumstances arise. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui asjaolud m&otilde;jutavad toetuse suurust, makstakse toetust uues suuruses asjaolude tekkimise kuule j&auml;rgnevast kuust. </eesti>
<inglise>If the circumstances affect the amount of a benefit, the benefit shall be paid in the new amount as of the month following the month in which such circumstances arise. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud toetuse maksmine l&otilde;petatakse lapse vanema tagaotsimise l&otilde;petamisele v&otilde;i isaduse tuvastamise kohtuotsusele j&auml;rgnevast kuust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Payment of an allowance granted pursuant to &sect; 7 of this Act shall be terminated as of the month following termination of the search of a parent or a court judgment on establishment of paternal filiation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Toetuse maksmine l&otilde;petatakse, kui toetus on m&auml;&auml;ratud seadusliku aluseta pensioniameti s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Payment of a benefit shall be terminated if the benefit is granted without legal basis by the fault of the Pension Board. </inglise>
<eesti>Toetuse maksmise l&otilde;petamise otsus saadetakse toetust saanud isikule posti teel viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates otsuse tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>A decision to terminate payment of a benefit shall be sent to the recipient of the benefit by post within five working days as of the date on which the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Peretoetuste saajal on &otilde;igus toetustest loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A recipient of family benefits has the right to decline the benefits. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste maksmine l&otilde;petatakse vastava kirjaliku taotluse esitamisele j&auml;rgnevast kuust. </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of the family benefits shall be terminated as of the month following the submission of a corresponding written application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste tagasin&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Reclamation of family benefits </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toetuste saaja teadliku valeandmete esitamise v&otilde;i peretoetuste saamist m&otilde;jutavate asjaolude mitteteatamise ilmnemisel n&otilde;utakse peretoetusteks enammakstud summad tagasi v&otilde;i tehakse tasaarvestus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If it becomes evident that a recipient of benefits has knowingly submitted false information or has failed to give notice of the circumstances which affect the grant of family benefits, the amounts of family benefits which are overpaid shall be reclaimed or set off. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui isik ei maksa alusetult saadud peretoetusi tagasi, v&otilde;idakse enammakstud summad pensionikomisjoni otsuse alusel talle etten&auml;htud peretoetustest kinni pidada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person fails to repay family benefits received without legal basis, the overpaid amounts may be deducted from the family benefits prescribed for him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnipeetav osa ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 20 protsenti isikule m&auml;&auml;ratud toetuste summast. </eesti>
<inglise>The amount to be withheld shall not exceed 20 per cent of the amount of benefits granted to the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui peretoetuste maksmine l&otilde;petatakse enne enammakstud summa t&auml;ielikku tasaarvestamist, tehakse isikule enammakstud summade tagasin&otilde;udmiseks ettekirjutus koos hoiatusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If payment of family benefits is terminated before the complete offsetting of the overpaid amount, a precept together with a warning shall be issued to the person for reclamation of the overpaid amounts. </inglise>
<eesti>Hoiatuses m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htaja jooksul ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral on pensioniametil &otilde;igus rakendada sunniraha asendust&auml;itmise ja sunniraha seaduses (RT I 2001, 50, 283) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon failure to comply with the precept within a term set out in the warning, the Pension Board has the right to impose penalty payment pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Substitutive Enforcement and Penalty Payment Act (RT I 2001, 50, 283). </inglise>
<eesti>Sunniraha &uuml;lemm&auml;&auml;r on 2000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>The upper limit of penalty payment is 2000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettekirjutus koos hoiatusega saadetakse toetusi saanud isikule posti teel viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse ja hoiatuse tegemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A precept together with a warning shall be sent to a recipient of benefits by post within five working days as of the date of issue of the precept and the warning. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Peretoetuste andmete kandmine registrisse </eesti>
<inglise>Entry of data concerning family benefits in register </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Andmed peretoetuste m&auml;&auml;ramise, m&auml;&auml;ramise aluste ja maksmise kohta kantakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse seaduse alusel moodustatud riikliku pensionikindlustuse registrisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Data concerning the grant, bases for grant and payment of family benefits shall be entered in the state pension insurance register established pursuant to the State Pension Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Andmete kandmine registrisse ja andmete saamine registrist toimub vastavalt andmekogude seadusele (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77), isikuandmete kaitse seadusele (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 50, 283) ja teistele seadustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Data shall be entered in and released from the register pursuant to the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 17, 77), the Personal Data Protection Act (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 50, 283) and other Acts. </inglise>
